snippet.textDisplay: Brazilian here. I'm not a chocolate girl, I'm more like a coffee milk. A lot of greens and purples and brown tones all over my red native American descended face. A lot of purple on my lips. But lately I am enjoying a natural look on my lips. And the key, for me, is to keep them moist. I use lip balm each couple of hours and my lips don't look like a corpse's lips anymore. In Brazil I never used balms, now in the Japanese dry winter's, I have at least one balm at each pocket.
